# Rule Naming and Organization

## Purpose
Define consistent naming and organization patterns for rules to improve discoverability and maintainability.

## File Structure
```
rules/V2/
├── 00-meta/          # Meta rules about rules
├── 10-architecture/  # High-level architecture decisions
├── 20-code-quality/  # Code quality and style
├── 30-patterns/      # Design patterns and implementations
└── 40-guidelines/    # General principles and practices
```

## Naming Conventions

### Files
- Use kebab-case for all file names
- Use `.mdc` extension for all rule files
- Prefix with number for ordering (e.g., `00-`, `01-`, etc.)
- Use descriptive, action-oriented names

Examples:
```
✅ 00-naming.mdc
✅ 01-error-handling.mdc
❌ errorHandling.mdc
❌ Error_Handling.mdc
```

### Rule Titles
- Use Title Case for main rule titles
- Use sentence case for sections
- Be concise but descriptive

Examples:
```
✅ # Error Handling Standards
✅ ## When to apply
❌ # ERROR HANDLING STANDARDS
❌ ## When To Apply
```

## Tags
Each rule should include relevant tags for better searchability:

```markdown
Tags: #category #specific-topic #related-concept
```

Example:
```markdown
Tags: #error-handling #typescript #validation
```

## Cross-References
Link related rules using relative paths:

```markdown
Related:
- [Type Safety](mdc:../20-code-quality/type-safety.mdc)
- [Error Patterns](mdc:../30-patterns/error-patterns.mdc)
```

## Machine-Readable Metadata
Include a YAML frontmatter section for Cursor LLM:

```yaml
---
priority: 1-5
applies_to: ["*.ts", "*.vue"]
triggers:
  - "error handling"
  - "try catch"
related_rules:
  - "type-safety"
  - "validation"
---
```

Tags: #meta #organization #naming #structure